'''1921年5月磁暴'''是威力巨大的一次[[日冕大量拋射|日冕大量拋射]]對地球磁層造成影響的重大事件。它發生在5月13日至15日，是[[第15太陽週期|第15太陽週期]]的一部分。此一事件發生在廣泛的應用互聯互通的電氣系統和一般電器依賴跨基礎結構發達之前，即使造成地面電流的強度超過造成北美洲東部大停電的[[1989年3月磁暴|1989年3月磁暴]]，所受的影響也僅限於某些部門<ref>{{cite web|url=http://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2009/21jan_severespaceweather/|title=Severe Space Weather - Social and Economic Impacts|author=Dr Tony Phillips|date=January 21, 2009|publisher=[[NASA|NASA]]|accessdate=December 18, 2012|archive-date=2014-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140414051544/http://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2009/21jan_severespaceweather/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在當時，科學家測量引起風暴的黑子在5月10日的大小是94,000乘21,000 平方英里（131,000乘33,800平方公里）<ref name=CDTM16>{{cite news|url=http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921o.pdf|title=Borealis Cause, Sun Spots, Will Diminish Today|newspaper=Chicago Daily Tribune|page=4|date=May 16, 1921|accessdate=December 19, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812123940/http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921o.pdf|archivedate=2014-08-12}}</ref><ref name=LATM16>{{cite news|url=http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921r.pdf|title=Sun Spots Vanishing|newspaper=The Los Angeles Times|pages=1 & 2|date=May 16, 1921|accessdate=December 19, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812124740/http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921r.pdf|archivedate=2014-08-12}}</ref>。

在美國東部有許多地區都能看見[[極光|極光]]，創造出明亮的夜空。[[電報|電報]]服務在美國是因為保險絲被燒斷而被拖慢，到14日午夜才因設備損壞而幾乎完全中斷。另一面，由於電離層的活躍使得越洋的無線電傳輸信號增強。電燈似乎沒有受到明顯的影響<ref name=NYTM15>{{cite news|url=http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921c.pdf|title=Sunspot Aurora Paralyses Wires|newspaper=New York Times|pages=1 & 3|date=May 15, 1921|accessdate=December 19, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022185813/http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921c.pdf|archivedate=2013-10-22}}</ref>。海底電纜也遭受磁暴的影響，歐洲也有電訊系統受到損壞的報導<ref name=NYTM17>{{cite news|url=http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921d.pdf|title=Cables Damaged by Sunspot Aurora|newspaper=New York Times|pages=1 & 4|date=May 17, 1921|accessdate=December 19, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812062659/http://www.solarstorms.org/NewsPapers/1921d.pdf|archivedate=2014-08-12}}</ref>，南半球也受到影響<ref>{{cite news|title=Aurora Borealis|author=|url=http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&d=HNS19210516.1.8&e=-------10--1----0--|newspaper=Hawera & Normanby Star|page=8|date=May 16, 1921|accessdate=December 18, 2012|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305141856/http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&d=HNS19210516.1.8&e=-------10--1----0--|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

